### Test Analytics Satisfaction Score Endpoint
### Prerequisites: You need a valid JWT token from a government user (officer/admin/super_admin)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000/api/v1
@token = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJzdWIiOiJlNDY5NjlmYS0zM2JiLTRhMzUtOTQ0Zi1lNmQ5NTdiZDJmYjciLCJyb2xlIjoiYWRtaW4iLCJuaXAiOiIxOTgwMDEwMTIwMDUwMTEwMDEiLCJhZ2VuY3lJZCI6IjAwMDAwMDAwLTAwMDAtMDAwMC0wMDAwLTAwMDAwMDAwMDAwMSIsImlhdCI6MTc3NjkxNzExNywiZXhwIjoxNzc2OTE4MDE3fQ.y2zPMk85xaqo0S4j4BW3acMJsFjWk1yfv56Si4NM4E8

### Test 1: Get satisfaction score for 30 days (default)
GET {{baseUrl}}/gov/analytics/satisfaction?period=30
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Test 2: Get satisfaction score for 90 days
GET {{baseUrl}}/gov/analytics/satisfaction?period=90
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Test 3: Get satisfaction score for 365 days
GET {{baseUrl}}/gov/analytics/satisfaction?period=365
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Test 4: Test without authentication (should fail with 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/gov/analytics/satisfaction?period=30

### Test 5: Test with invalid period (should use default 30)
GET {{baseUrl}}/gov/analytics/satisfaction?period=invalid
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Test 6: Test without period parameter (should use default 30)
GET {{baseUrl}}/gov/analytics/satisfaction
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected Response Format:
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "data": {
#     "averageRating": 4.2,
#     "totalRatings": 156
#   }
# }

### Expected Response When No Ratings:
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "data": {
#     "averageRating": null,
#     "totalRatings": 0
#   }
# }

### Notes:
# - Joins satisfaction_ratings with reports table
# - Filters by report createdAt within period
# - Applies role-based filtering (officer sees only assigned, admin sees agency, super_admin sees all)
# - Returns null for averageRating if no ratings exist
# - Rounds average to 1 decimal place
# - Results are cached for 5 minutes with key pattern: analytics:satisfaction:{agencyId}:{period}
# - Rating scale: 1-5
